sed spells on dedicated hotkeys with my enchanter, if it were technically possible.<br>
<br>
Aldrahn had a good tip, in case you missed it. When memorizing/forgetting spells, you don't have to use the vertical row of 8 gems. You can right-click once on your spell hotkey to forget a spell, and also memorize spells by left-clicking your spell in your spellbook, then left-clicking again directly on a hotkey that has an empty spell gem slot.<br>
<br>
I have a dedicated &quot;swap&quot; slot, that rotates between pet summon, dagger summon, miscellaneous summon (bandages, arrows, heatstone, etc. as needed). I chose the slot that normally houses Malise to do this, as that is the spell I'm least likely to need in an emergency should we get jumped while fooling about with the miscellaneous stuff.<br>
<br>
Once you get a hotkey setup that you are comfortable with, do yourself a favor and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> never change it</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. As you level, the exact spells may change a bit, for example as your preferred nuke gets upgraded, but always keep that 'preferred nuke' slot in the same place.<br>
<br>
Also, it's very helpful to take the time to defining a social for each /pet command, even if you think you'll never use it, and dedicate a hotkey page to those commands.<br>
<br>
Here's my line-up of hotkeys:<br>
1 - Primary nuke (currently shock of spikes)<br>
2 - (whoops I forget! used to be /pet attack <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
3 - Secondary nuke (currently bolt of flame)<br>
4 - damage shield<br>
5 - /pet report health<br>
6 - /assist hotkey OR pet healing spell when soloing<br>
7 - Malise (or current misc. spell)<br>
8 - Gate<br>
9 - /pet back off<br>
0 - /pet attack<br>
<br>
Yeah yeah I know it's not logical, but these things develop for you over time, and once you get used to something it's not really worth it to change (unless it's not working for you).<br>
<br>
I also have my shielding spell on a separate hotkey page, since I hate noticing the blinking too late and winding up at less than full health if it takes me too long to rememorize and cast.<br>
<br>
Pet buff and healing spells are also on dedicated hotkeys on a separate page, as usually they're not needed at a moment's notice, except for the healing which trades places with /assist on the first page when soloing.<br>
<br>
At level 12, I'd definitely have the following spells available:<br>
- Shock of Blades<br>
- Flame Bolt<br>
- Column of Fire<br>
- Burnout<br>
- Renew Elements<br>
- Shield of Fire<br>
- Lesser Shielding<br>
- Gate<br>
<br>
Depending on what you're fighting, you may want to swap out a bit. For example if you are in lavastorm, flame bolt isn't going to do you much good, but cancel magic (to get rid of damage shields) and ward summoned will be worth their weight in platinum.<br>
<br>
Welcome to the world of summoning, enjoy your stay! <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

