The other slots I swapped out with: 1. sense heading /loc  and bind wounds hotkey that I used for travel and (obviously) binding people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  2. Assist hotkey 3. sometimes an inventory slot.<br>
<br>
Page two was my setup page (before cornucopia and everfont it was a pain summoning everything) where I keep the inventory slot with the bag I keep the focus items in, AND a primary hand slot (makes swaping them out real fast). Also had spell gems for summoning stuff, but I don't use them as much anymore <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now that you can type to cast spells, I'll probably end up using that if I'm blinded (not to hard to remember /cast 1 or /cast 20 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
