<br>
First, I find the keyboard to be easier than the mouse. So anything I can move to keyboard functionality rather than mouse is better for me. Yes, I even use F8 to target baddies and F7 to target players. And of course F2-F6 for party members.<br>
<br>
Second, the mouse pointer gets lost easily due to video lag, spell effects going off everywhere, or even backgrounds where the pointer kind of blends in. In some situations you just don't have the time to take 5 seconds to locate your mouse pointer before casting a spell.<br>
<br>
Third, the keyboard layout never changes. When I want to cast Gate, I know exactly where the &quot;8&quot; key is. The mouse pointer could be anywhere on the screen, so there's a time variable in casting the spell.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the spell gems are just too darned small in higher resolutions for under-fire casting. It's too easy to miss the gems, or cast the wrong spell. <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

