<br>
Here is for solo:<br>
1. /pet attack<br>
2. /pet back off<br>
3. /assist  (toggled between pet and mob)<br>
4. /g Incoming: %t   (in case I am grouped with no tank and I am pulling)<br>
5. macro to firesheild the pet and retarget mob<br>
  /pet target<br>
  /cast 2 (fireshield)<br>
  /assist<br>
6. shock spell or anto-summonned spell<br>
  or heal pet macro (when fighting hard hitters)<br>
    /pet target<br>
    /cast 3 (renew elements slot)<br>
    /assist<br>
7. slot 8 in inventory (usually has a mod rod)<br>
8. non-bolt DD<br>
9. ranged attack (throwing daggers to see if a bolt will hit)<br>
0. bolt spell<br>
<br>
For group use with a tank<br>
1. /pet attack<br>
2. /pet back off<br>
3. /assist<br>
4. /assist &lt;tank name here&gt;<br>
5. fireshield the tank macro<br>
  /target &lt;tank name here&gt;<br>
  /pause 20,/cast 2  (firesheild, delay to make sure the tank was selected, sometimes /target does not work is tank is not very near)<br>
  /assist<br>
6. Bind Wounds or fast casting DD if fighting casters<br>
7. Inventory slot 8 (with mod rod)<br>
8. non-bolt biggest DD (level 8 or high depends on what I am fighting)<br>
9. ranged attack (for checking bolt hit) or a silly macro (depends on group)<br>
  /say You will not eveade me %t!<br>
0. Biggest bolt (another silly macro here if in a dungeon and bolts are not useful)<br>
  /say Time to die %t!<br>
<br>
Travel<br>
1. /pet attack<br>
2. /follow<br>
3. /assist<br>
4. /corpse<br>
5. /loc<br>
6. Sense Heading<br>
7. Hide<br>
8. Bind Wound<br>
9. Ranged attack (for lack of anythig else interesting)<br>
0. /cast 8 (Gate)<br>
